div.p:
Although planting doth chiefly depend upon the bleſſing and providence of God,1 Cor. 3.6. (without which no benefit can be expected) yet God who ordaineth the end, appointeth alſo the means conducible thereunto; not that men ſhould reſt in the means appointed, but that they waiting upon God in the uſe of meanes ſhould expect his bleſſing thereupon of his grace and mercy: according to the ſaying,


Reſt not in meanes, uſe meanes Gods gifts to gain;

God gives the end, and meanes his ends t'attain.
